231204_redox_corrections

2023-12-04

Goal

Detail the steps used to go from raw redox values collected by SWAP sensors during TEMPEST to final Eh values to be used on poster / in paper.

Raw data

I know it gets old looking at time-series, but Id like to present ALL the data in completely raw format first, so that were all starting at 0. Note the dashed vertical line below marks the start of the last sensors we got online (seawater plot) so that were starting a consistent datetime origin across plots:

Freshwater

Behavior looks very similar between reference probes (ra and rb).

Estuarine

As with Freshwater, we see similar behavior between reference probes.

Control

And this is where things get funky. Based on behavior in the other two plots, and particularly at depth, we dont see clear diurnal signals in the data. While Control might be more susceptible due to thinner canopy, Im hard-pressed to believe that daily cycles of 200 mV is real, and happening consistently at all depths.

Decision: Use ra as reference

Binning

First, lets average across the 5 sensors at each depth-plot combo and plot as boxplots for reference. Weve got some issues of zeros that are clearly erroneous. Super fortunately, they only occur in Control and Seawater, neither of which have sensors that realistically reach zero (and no values are exactly 0 in Freshwater), so we will scrub 0s then interpolate to gap-fill a total of 16 values (4 timestamp/plot combos x 4 depths).

Decision: Include all sensors, use means, and scrub then gap-fill 0s

Binned but with errors

Binned with errors gap-filled

Corrections

Based on my nascent understanding of redox, there are several potential corrections, including

  • changes in temperature
  • soil pH
  • conversion to Eh units

Ill do the correction for temperature at the same time as the conversion to SHE using \(Eh=ORP-0.718*T+224.41\). This equation was pulled from Faustos pre-print (see L154) which he applied to both soil and water redox sensors.

Decision: use Faustos correction equation for final units

Questions for yall

  1. What corrections am I missing that need to be incorporated?
  2. Does the equation used to correct make sense?
  3. Smell test: what feels wrong and what feels right?
